page.title: 05Alwyn North NAA Jacket.
page.content: The Alwyn North NAA jacket was built by RGC in their yard at Methil for Total Oil Marine and Elf UK.This 140m high steel jacket,weighing 18,500 tonnes,now supports a drilling and accommodation rig in the Alwyn North Field,160km North East of Shetland. On May 1 1985,it was towed by barge to that position,launched and upended and then fixed in place with eight piles at each corner leg.These were driven about 40m into the sea bed to ensure stability. This huge construction has towered over Denbeath for almost two years and, now that is has gone,people are missing it. Before long,however,work is to be started on another jacket and the skyline around Denbeath will soon look familiar again.
